body:
In that case the `__version__` isn't set correctly somewhere else because I compiled Pytorch from source on the `0.4.1` branch and here is what I get:
```
$ python
Python 3.6.5 |Anaconda, Inc.| (default, Apr 29 2018, 16:14:56)
[GCC 7.2.0] on linux
Type "help", "copyright", "credits" or "license" for more information.
>>> import torch
>>> torch.__version__
'0.5.0a0+a24163a'
```
